    <abstract id="aspace_31786745b43a1859bbdbdf4a42f5c668">The Flatbush Fire Company was established by the Board of Trustees of the town of Flatbush (later the Flatbush neighborhood of Brooklyn) in September 1829. The collection includes a bound minute book, loose minutes of meetings, rules and regulations, and appointments of firemen. Also included is one certificate of appointment to the Fire Department of William Algeo, Jr.</abstract>
